[{"id":41288,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>As the disc is revolving in circular motion about an axis passing through centre&nbsp;and perpendicular to its plane, thus centrifugal force must act on it. The forces acting on disc is shown below.</p><p>&nbsp;From FBD</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e19d503f-af31-481d-a3ec-b7bbd2925fe0-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 128px;\" /></p><p>For circular motion,&nbsp;frictional force must balance the required centripetal force.</p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#8805;</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>R</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>&#8804;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41399,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["16","6","4","8"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\mathrm{T}-60 \\mathrm{~g}=60 \\mathrm{a} ; \\mathrm{T}=3000 \\mathrm{~N} ; \\quad \\therefore \\mathrm{a}=4 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41208,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mu g}{R}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{2 \\mu R}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{2 g}{\\mu R}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{\\mu R}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Consider the mass $M$ in the frame of the rotating drum. The forces acting on the mass are:<br>1. Weight $Mg$ acting vertically downwards.<br>2. Normal reaction $N$ from the wall acting towards the center, which provides the centripetal force: $N = M\\omega^2 R$.<br>3. Frictional force $f$ acting vertically upwards to balance the weight.<br>For the mass to remain stuck to the wall, the frictional force must balance the weight: $f = Mg$.<br>The maximum available static friction is $f_{max} = \\mu N = \\mu M\\omega^2 R$.<br>To prevent slipping, we must have $f_{max} \\ge Mg$.<br>$\\mu M\\omega^2 R \\ge Mg$<br>$\\omega^2 \\ge \\frac{g}{\\mu R}$<br>$\\omega \\ge \\sqrt{\\frac{g}{\\mu R}}$<br>The minimum value of $\\omega$ is $\\sqrt{\\frac{g}{\\mu R}}$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (21 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41204,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} \\mathrm{mg}$","$\\mathrm{mg}$","$\\frac{1}{2} m \\mathrm{~g}$","$\\sqrt{3} \\mathrm{mg}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"A chain of mass $m$ hangs between two fixed points at the same level with inclination $30°$ at support points.<br>Consider equilibrium of one half of the chain (mass $m/2$): <br>Horizontal equilibrium: $T_0 = T_1\\cos(30°) = T_1 \\cdot \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}$<br>Vertical equilibrium: $T_1\\sin(30°) = \\frac{m}{2}g$<br>From vertical equation: $T_1 \\cdot \\frac{1}{2} = \\frac{mg}{2}$, giving $T_1 = mg$<br>Substituting into horizontal equation: $T_0 = mg \\cdot \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2}mg$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41247,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The equation for velocity is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Thus, the acceleration is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>The force is written as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mover><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p><p>Comparing it with the given value of force,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41254,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a21649b9-42a3-47f7-bb53-49a4347a74e8-9895376_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 259px;\" /></p><p>From geometry,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p><p>For equilibrium,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (30 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41281,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/109b4afb-eaef-49da-b610-70468789cbbd-image.png\" style=\"width: 240px; height: 183px;\" /></p><p>Equation for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>M</mi><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equation for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Adding both equation we get,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Now, tension&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mi>M</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41224,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$1.47 \\mathrm{~N}$","$147 \\mathrm{~N}$","$14.7 \\mathrm{~N}$","$1470 \\mathrm{~N}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/25AblWAw4R5-voSx3Pb2797SleHtXxuE6QZSnvziJ7s.original.fullsize.png\"><br />$F_k=\\mu_k N=0.3 \\times 50 \\times 9.8=147 N$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41380,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$2 \\sin \\phi$","$2 \\cos \\phi$","$2 \\tan \\phi$","$\\tan \\phi$"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/XkpvivO_XIZcidquvcUicnkbXBI0aCMNs1OZVzxu2g0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n$m g s \\sin \\phi=\\mu m g \\cos \\phi \\cdot \\frac{s}{2}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":41339,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math><mn>23</mn><mi> </mi><mi>N</mi></math>","<math><mn>25</mn><mi> </mi><mi>N</mi></math>","<math><mn>18</mn><mi> </mi><mi>N</mi></math>","<math><mn>32</mn><mi> </mi><mi>N</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/gdlvnfsfhlsvhajkpszfhrhhfnqfnrwijincinquemltzvgvyz.png\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c299e4f8-7fba-49b6-a699-2dc3faddff0f-image.png\" /><br />Block will be at rest<br /><br /><math><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mrow><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>f</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">cos</mi></mrow><mo>&#8289;</mo><mrow><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mrow></math><br /><br />( <math><mo>&#8757;</mo></math> To get <math><mi>P</mi></math> minimum friction must be minimum)<br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0.6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mi>N</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41268,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given that the mass of the air&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>&nbsp;and it escapes in time&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>&nbsp;with velocity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p><p>The average force on the balloon can be given as,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>dyne</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41257,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d8f03af1-56ac-4a4a-aee1-0911619dfbd8-9895034.PNG\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 130px;\" /></p><p>For the second case when body is moving with constant velocity, we can write</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Now this velocity if the final velocity for the first case, therefore</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>20</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>20</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Hence, required force will be</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41392,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["Both the scales read $\\mathrm{M} \\mathrm{kg}$ each","The scale of the lower one reads $\\mathrm{M} \\mathrm{kg}$ and of the upper one zero","The reading of the two scales can be anything but the sum of the reading will be $\\mathrm{M} \\mathrm{kg}$","Both the scales read $\\mathrm{M} / 2 \\mathrm{~kg}$ each"],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":41376,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$12 \\mathrm{~kg}$ and $13 \\mathrm{~kg}$","$5 \\mathrm{~kg}$ and $5 \\mathrm{~kg}$","$5 \\mathrm{~kg}$ and $12 \\mathrm{~kg}$","$5 \\mathrm{~kg}$ and $13 \\mathrm{~kg}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\mathrm{T}_2 \\cos \\left(\\frac{\\pi}{2}-\\theta\\right)=\\mathrm{T}_1 \\cos \\theta \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{T}_1 \\cos \\theta=\\mathrm{T}_2 \\sin \\theta$\n$\\mathrm{T}_1 \\sin \\theta+\\mathrm{T}_2 \\cos \\theta=13$.\n$\\because \\mathrm{OC}=\\mathrm{CA}=\\mathrm{CB}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\angle \\mathrm{AOC}=\\angle \\mathrm{OAC}$ and $\\angle \\mathrm{COB}=\\angle \\mathrm{OBC}$\n$\\therefore \\sin \\theta=\\sin \\mathrm{A}=\\frac{5}{13}$ and $\\cos \\theta=\\frac{12}{13}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\frac{\\mathrm{T}_1}{\\mathrm{~T}_2}=\\frac{5}{12} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{T}_1=\\frac{5}{12} \\mathrm{~T}_2$\n$\\mathrm{~T}_2\\left(\\frac{5}{12} \\cdot \\frac{5}{13}+\\frac{12}{13}\\right)=13$\n$\\mathrm{~T}_2\\left(\\frac{169}{12 \\cdot 13}\\right)=13$\n$\\mathrm{~T}_2=12 \\mathrm{~kgs} . \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{T}_1=5 \\mathrm{~kgs}$.\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ubnXLnGoIqTq0JkHH7kEiA-ovgVga3mpqI8iZyK_L7g.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":41391,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$\\frac{\\mathrm{Pm}}{\\mathrm{M}+\\mathrm{m}}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{Pm}}{\\mathrm{M}-\\mathrm{m}}$","$P$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{PM}}{\\mathrm{M}+\\mathrm{m}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Since the displacement for both block and rope is same so, the acceleration must be same for both\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7EriFigkOEAuJP-b6bkAWXuLK3VCK_ebKjnF0uGY3Yo.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a2IrsKMGEx-TUKk3aB3Dt3TAB93AxBmrOCSaHKHXHWc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n$\\Rightarrow \\mathrm{p}=(\\mathrm{m}+\\mathrm{M}) \\mathrm{a} \\quad \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{\\mathrm{P}}{\\mathrm{m}+\\mathrm{M}}$\n$\\mathrm{T}=\\mathrm{M} \\cdot \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{\\mathrm{PM}}{\\mathrm{m}+\\mathrm{M}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":41365,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$12 \\mathrm{~N}$","$6 \\mathrm{~N}$","zero","$18 \\mathrm{~N}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Here, rate of fall of sand on conveyer belt,\n$$\n\\frac{d m}{d t}=2 \\mathrm{~kg} \\mathrm{~s}^{-1}\n$$\nConveyer belt speed $v=3 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$ Force $F=$ ?\n$$\nF=v \\frac{d m}{d t}=3 \\times 2=6 \\mathrm{~N}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":41382,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$3 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$15 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$5 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","$10 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$a=\\frac{k x}{m}=10 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":41363,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$-\\frac{\\alpha v^2}{2 M}$","$-\\frac{\\alpha v^2}{M}$","$-\\alpha v^2$","$-\\frac{2 \\alpha v^2}{M}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"$a_{\\text {inst }}=\\frac{\\alpha \\mathrm{V}^2}{\\mathrm{M}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (26 May Online)","image":null},{"id":41329,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1.7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1.9</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1.5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2.0</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math><mn>4000</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>P</mi></math><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>746</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4000</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>20000</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>V</mi></math><br /><math><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo></math><math><mn>1.9&nbsp;</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m&nbsp;</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (07 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41214,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{T}=\\mathrm{K}\\left(\\ell-\\ell_0\\right) \\\\ & \\Rightarrow 5=\\mathrm{K}\\left(1.4-\\ell_0\\right) \\\\ & \\Rightarrow 7=\\mathrm{K}\\left(1.56-\\ell_0\\right) \\\\ & \\Rightarrow \\frac{5}{1.4-\\ell_0}=\\frac{7}{1.56-\\ell_0} \\\\ & \\therefore \\ell_0=1 \\mathrm{~m}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41360,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$144 \\mathrm{~N}$","$96 \\mathrm{~N}$","$240 \\mathrm{~N}$","$192 \\mathrm{~N}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"Acceleration produced in upward direction\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{a}=\\frac{\\mathrm{F}}{\\mathrm{M}_1+\\mathrm{M}_2+\\text { Mass of metal rod }} \\\\\n& =\\frac{480}{20+12+8}=12 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nTension at the mid point\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathrm{T} & =\\left(\\mathrm{M}_2+\\frac{\\text { Mass of rod }}{2}\\right) \\mathrm{a} \\\\\n& =(12+4) \\times 12=192 \\mathrm{~N}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":41397,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["8 : 1","9 : 7","4 : 3","5 : 3"],"answer":1,"solution":"$a=\\frac{m_1-m_2}{m_1+m_2} g ; \\frac{1}{8}=\\frac{m_1-m_2}{m_1+m_2} \\Rightarrow m_1: m_2=9: 7$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":41201,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$\\sqrt{\\frac{2 L}{g \\sin \\theta-a_{0} \\cos \\theta}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{4 L}{g \\cos ^{2} \\theta-a_{0} \\sin \\theta \\cos \\theta}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{2 L}{g \\sin 2 \\theta-a_{0}(1+\\cos 2 \\theta)}}$","$\\sqrt{\\frac{4 L}{g \\sin 2 \\theta-a_{0}(1+\\cos 2 \\theta)}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<br>$mg\\sin\\theta - ma_0\\cos\\theta = ma$<br>$a = g\\sin\\theta - a_0\\cos\\theta$<br>Now using,<br>$S = ut + \\dfrac{1}{2}a_{down}t^2$<br>$\\dfrac{L}{\\cos\\theta} = \\dfrac{1}{2}(g\\sin\\theta - a_0\\cos\\theta)t^2$<br>$t = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2L}{g\\sin\\theta\\cos\\theta - a_0\\cos^2\\theta}}$<br>$t = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{4L}{g\\sin 2\\theta - a_0(1 + \\cos 2\\theta)}}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (28 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41194,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$0.33$","$0.67$","$1$","$0.5$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Let us analyze the forces acting on blocks $P$ and $Q$ in the non-inertial frame of reference of the cube $S$, which is moving to the right with an acceleration $a = \\dfrac{g}{2} = 5 \\text{ m/s}^2$.<br><br>In this frame, a pseudo force acts on both blocks towards the left.<br><br>For block $P$ (mass $m_P = 2 \\text{ kg}$):<br>The forces in the horizontal direction are the tension $T$ in the string (acting towards the right) and the pseudo force $F_{pP}$ (acting towards the left). Since block $P$ is stationary relative to the cube and there is no friction on the top surface:<br>$T = m_P a = 2 \\times 5 = 10 \\text{ N}$<br><br>For block $Q$ (mass $m_Q = 1.5 \\text{ kg}$):<br>The horizontal forces are the normal reaction $N$ from the side surface of the cube (acting towards the right) and the pseudo force $F_{pQ}$ (acting towards the left). Since block $Q$ is stationary horizontally relative to the cube:<br>$N = m_Q a = 1.5 \\times 5 = 7.5 \\text{ N}$<br><br>The vertical forces acting on block $Q$ are the downward gravitational force $m_Q g$, the upward tension $T$, and the frictional force $f$.<br>The downward force is $m_Q g = 1.5 \\times 10 = 15 \\text{ N}$.<br>Since $m_Q g > T$ ($15 \\text{ N} > 10 \\text{ N}$), the block has a tendency to slide downwards, so the static friction $f$ must act upwards.<br>For vertical equilibrium of block $Q$:<br>$T + f = m_Q g$<br>$10 + f = 15 \\Rightarrow f = 5 \\text{ N}$<br><br>To keep the block stationary, the required friction must be less than or equal to the maximum static friction ($f \\le \\mu N$). Assuming the limiting case to find the value of $\\mu$:<br>$\\mu N = f$<br>$\\mu (7.5) = 5$<br>$\\mu = \\dfrac{5}{7.5} = \\dfrac{2}{3} \\approx 0.67$<br><br>Answer: $0.67$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41279,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Let velocity of water jet be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p><p>So, force applied is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Acceleration of block,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41310,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1d9e0a5e-5430-4268-a33d-31bbd11ec4fa-image.png\" style=\"width: 203px; height: 197px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>90</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (17 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41300,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>100</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>400</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>100</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>100</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>400</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>100</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>400</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>400</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mover><mi>F</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mover><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mi>dt</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>At&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sec</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>[</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>]</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mover><mi>r</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>400</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mn>100</mn><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41313,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>K</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>K</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>K</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>K</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed268a62-7d72-48b0-8b11-de8b70a2593a-image.png\" style=\"width: 310px; height: 224px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>F</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>K</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mi>g</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41367,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$(1-f) \\omega_1=f \\omega$","$\\omega_1=\\omega_2$ and independent of $f$","$f \\omega_1=(1-f) \\omega_2$","$\\omega_1=\\omega_2$ and depend on $f$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Angular velocity is the angular displacement per unit time i.e., $\\omega=\\frac{\\Delta \\theta}{\\Delta t}$ Here $w_1=w_2$ and independent of $f$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":41206,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"For the 8 kg block (C) to move with constant velocity, $F_{net} = 0$.<br><br>Friction forces acting:<br>- Between C and ground: $f = \\mu(m_A + m_B + m_C)g = 0.5 \\times (4+6+8) \\times 10 = 90$ N<br>- Between C and B: $f = \\mu(m_A + m_B)g = 0.5 \\times (4+6) \\times 10 = 50$ N<br><br>For the 6 kg block (B):<br>$T = f_{\\text{B on ground}} + f_{\\text{A on B}}$<br>$T = \\mu(m_A + m_B)g \\cdot \\frac{m_B}{m_A+m_B} + \\mu \\cdot m_A \\cdot g$<br>$T = 20 + 50 = 70$ N<br><br>For the 8 kg block (C):<br>$F = 90 + T + 50 = 90 + 70 + 50 = 210$ N","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41285,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The figure shows the tension acting on each string in the system.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f7da3da6-9f53-409f-bc9d-ebd55b2e4fd0-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 297px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8721;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>&#183;</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>T</mi><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>T</mi><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41196,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$5/3$","$2/3$","$3/5$","$2/5$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Let the acceleration of the system be $a$. The total mass on the right side is $m_2 + m_3 = 4 + 6 = 10$ kg, and the mass on the left side is $m_1 = 4$ kg. Since $10$ kg $> 4$ kg, the right side accelerates downwards and the left side accelerates upwards.<br><br>The common acceleration $a$ of the system is given by:<br>$a = \\dfrac{(m_2 + m_3) - m_1}{m_1 + m_2 + m_3} g$<br>$a = \\dfrac{10 - 4}{4 + 4 + 6} g = \\dfrac{6}{14} g = \\dfrac{3}{7} g$<br><br>For mass $m_1$, the equation of motion is:<br>$T_1 - m_1 g = m_1 a$<br>$T_1 = m_1(g + a) = 4 \\left(g + \\dfrac{3}{7}g\\right) = 4 \\left(\\dfrac{10}{7}g\\right) = \\dfrac{40}{7}g$<br><br>For mass $m_3$, the equation of motion is:<br>$m_3 g - T_2 = m_3 a$<br>$T_2 = m_3(g - a) = 6 \\left(g - \\dfrac{3}{7}g\\right) = 6 \\left(\\dfrac{4}{7}g\\right) = \\dfrac{24}{7}g$<br><br>The ratio of the tensions is:<br>$\\dfrac{T_1}{T_2} = \\dfrac{\\dfrac{40}{7}g}{\\dfrac{24}{7}g} = \\dfrac{40}{24} = \\dfrac{5}{3}$<br><br>Answer: $5/3$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (05 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":41260,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>60</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/479b98e0-10ba-4f82-8983-ee5133203e96-9894326_2.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 196px;\" /></p><p>The forces acting on block&nbsp;is shown in above figure.</p><p>Here, normal force,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>cos</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>&nbsp;and frictional force,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi></math>.</p><p>Balancing the force along incline, we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Now, the forces acting on block to just push it up on inclined plane is shown below.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cdb67a62-81c3-4fe0-b7b6-376572ea7e21-9894326_3.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 196px;\" /></p><p>Balancing the force along incline, we have</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>N</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Given,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#956;</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":41378,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$300 \\mathrm{~N}$","$150 \\mathrm{~N}$","$3 \\mathrm{~N}$","$30 \\mathrm{~N}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$(m v-0) \\Rightarrow 0.15 \\times 20$\n$\\mathrm{F}=\\frac{3}{0.1}=30 \\mathrm{~N}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2006","image":null},{"id":41209,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws of Motion","question":"","options":["$\\vec{v}=4 \\hat{i}-\\frac{3}{2} \\hat{j} \\quad \\vec{r}=\\frac{6}{5} \\hat{i}-\\hat{j}$","$\\vec{v}=3 \\hat{i}+\\frac{3}{2} \\hat{j} \\quad \\vec{r}=\\frac{6}{5} \\hat{i}+\\hat{j}$","$\\vec{v}=4 \\hat{i}-\\frac{3}{2} \\hat{j} \\quad \\vec{r}=\\frac{8}{5} \\hat{i}-\\hat{j}$","$\\vec{v}=4 \\hat{i}+\\frac{5}{2} \\hat{j} \\quad \\vec{r}=\\frac{8}{5} \\hat{i}+2 \\hat{j}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given $\\vec{F} = (4t^3\\hat{i} - 3t\\hat{j})$ N, m = 4 kg<br>$\\vec{a} = \\frac{\\vec{F}}{m} = t^3\\hat{i} - \\frac{3t}{4}\\hat{j}$<br>Integrating with $\\vec{v}(0) = 0$:<br>$\\vec{v} = \\frac{t^4}{4}\\hat{i} - \\frac{3t^2}{8}\\hat{j}$<br>At $t = 2$: $\\vec{v} = \\frac{16}{4}\\hat{i} - \\frac{12}{8}\\hat{j} = 4\\hat{i} - \\frac{3}{2}\\hat{j}$<br>Integrating with $\\vec{r}(0) = 0$:<br>$\\vec{r} = \\frac{t^5}{20}\\hat{i} - \\frac{t^3}{8}\\hat{j}$<br>At $t = 2$: $\\vec{r} = \\frac{32}{20}\\hat{i} - \\frac{8}{8}\\hat{j} = \\frac{8}{5}\\hat{i} - \\hat{j}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (21 January Shift 1)","image":null}]